---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
001 Virtual destructors
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
whenever you are dealing with inheritance, you should make your destructors virtual
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
002 Late binding
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Function Pointer is a kind of Late Binding
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
003 vtable: virtual function/method table
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
every class that uses virtual functions (or is derived from a class that uses virtual 
functions) is given it's own virtual table.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
004 pure virtual function(abstract function)  vs. abstract base class
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
a pure virtual function (or abstract function) that has no body at all! A pure virtual 
function simply acts as a placeholder that is meant to be redefined by derived classes.
---------
firstly, any class with one or more pure virtual functions becomes an abstract base class, 
which means that it can not be instantiated!
Second, any derived class must define a body for this function, or that derived class 
will be considered an abstract base class as well.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
005 Interface
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
An interface class is a class that has no members variables, and where all of the 
functions are pure virtual!
